<font color="#FF0000">BACKGROUND FOR PROF GRIVETTI</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jan 14  0:33:22 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Professor Grivetti, <br>
 I visited this site for the first time today. Would dearly love to be able to take your course, if only to get a fresh perspective. For the past 4 years I have been going into Philadelphia public and parochial high schools to teach a period on the Vietnam War. As you can well imagine; I hardly scratch the surface. <br><br>
 Came out of college with a BS in Geography (strong in landforms and climate). Became an aerial surveilence officer in military intelligence. Was assigned to the 172nd Military Intelligence Company, 173rd Airborne Brigade at LZ English, northern Binh Dinh province from July 68 to July 69. In Vietnam I was in charge of an aerial imagery interpretation section and flew hand held photo missions in anything I could find that was flying. Spent a large amount of off duty time working on court martial cases. Would like to go into detail about my experience in the future, but don't want to clog up the website. 
<p><code>-- turtle@plantaganet.com  (Gerald Alan Ney, The Herd, 68-69) </code><p>


